# Northstone App UI — Shadcn + Bedrock (Cursor)

When the task is **a whole page, site section stack, or greenfield UI flow** (not a one-line tweak), **read and follow** the project skill:

1. **`.claude/skills/bedrock/SKILL.md`** (skill id **`northstone-app-ui`** — same content as **[northstone-app-ui](https://github.com/Jacknelson6/northstone-app-ui)** for multi-repo use)
2. **`.claude/skills/bedrock/references/single-prompt-playbook.md`** (checklist — do not skip verify)
3. **`.claude/skills/bedrock/references/design-doctrine.md`** (typography, delight, cohesion)
4. **`.claude/skills/bedrock/references/shadcn-blocks-pipeline.md`** when running `npx shadcn add`

**Pipeline:** Shadcn blocks/primitives **first** (structure, a11y) → then **one** strong design direction (type + spacing) → then **Bedrock/React Bits** only for **1–2 deliberate surprises** (never wallpaper).

**Non‑negotiables**

- **Typography leads:** Pick an explicit pairing + scale before animation. No default Inter-only stack for marketing surfaces unless the product already mandates it.
- **Delight budget:** At most **one** hero‑level surprise (e.g. split headline **or** ambient background **or** one scroll choreo — not all three).
- **No magnetic hovers:** Never Magnet / MagnetLines / cursor-pull UI — see `design-doctrine.md`.
- **Fit over novelty:** Every block must feel like **one product**; if a section fights the last, simplify.
- **End state:** `npm run build` + `npm run lint` after substantive UI.

Upstream React Bits source: **[github.com/Jacknelson6/bedrock](https://github.com/Jacknelson6/bedrock)** → `~/.claude/skills/bedrock` if installed.
